This license allows self-hosted use of Push Booster, including internal business use that helps you earn revenue from your own traffic, while prohibiting resale, hosted access, white-label use and competing commercial products based on Push Booster.

## 1. Definitions

"Software" means the Push Booster source code, documentation, examples, assets and other materials distributed with this license.

"You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this license.

"Your Organization" means You and any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with You.

"Internal Use" means use of the Software by You or Your Organization for your own operations, including operating your own web-push traffic, campaigns, subscribers, analytics and media buying workflows.

"Commercial Product" means any product, service, hosted offering, managed service, SaaS, platform, white-label system, marketplace, reseller offering or paid access offering that is based on, includes, wraps, exposes, hosts or substantially competes with the Software.

## 2. Permitted Use

Subject to this license, You may:

- use, run and self-host the Software for personal use;
- use, run and self-host the Software for Internal Use;
- use the Software to operate your own traffic, campaigns and subscriber base, including revenue-generating traffic;
- study, review, test and evaluate the Software;
- modify the Software for your own permitted use;
- make backup copies and internal copies for deployment, security, testing and operations.

## 3. Prohibited Use

You may not, without a separate written commercial license from the licensor:

- sell, rent, lease, sublicense or resell the Software;
- provide the Software as a hosted service, SaaS, managed service or paid access service;
- provide third parties with access to the Software as a product or service;
- build, market or distribute a Commercial Product based on the Software;
- offer white-label, marketplace, agency-hosted or reseller access to the Software;
- use the Software to provide push-platform services for third-party customers as your product;
- remove or obscure copyright, license or attribution notices;
- use the Software in a way that violates applicable law.

## 4. Distribution

You may share unmodified copies of the Software for noncommercial evaluation if this license and all copyright notices are included.

You may not publicly distribute modified versions, forks, binaries, containers or hosted deployments of the Software without a separate written license from the licensor, except where required by applicable law.

